{
  "message": "test(fuzz): expand ft-serialize fuzz coverage \u2014 14 new state-dict seeds, new safetensors target\n\nDeep work option (D): extend the fuzz infrastructure that 42945e2 +\n37dd98b stood up.\n\nNative FTSV state-dict corpus (`fuzz/corpus/ft_serialize_state_dict/`):\nadds 14 structured seeds covering edge cases the prior 4-seed corpus\ndidn't reach:\n\n  rank-0 F64 / rank-0 F32 scalars\n  zero-numel tensor (shape [3, 0, 5])\n  large 1D F32 (1000 elements; chunked-read path)\n  4D F32 [2,3,4,5] (multi-dim ndim path)\n  multi-tensor (F64 + F32 + F16 in one record)\n  F16 NaN payload (0x7e00)\n  BF16 negative-zero payload (0x8000)\n  long-key (60-byte tensor name)\n  empty state dict + trailing garbage\n  truncated payload (claims numel=2, supplies 4 bytes for f64)\n  invalid magic (FTSW)\n  future version (version=2 vs FT_STATE_FORMAT_VERSION=1)\n  unknown dtype tag (255)\n\nBrings the corpus from 4 -> 18 seeds, hitting every distinct dtype\ndispatch arm, both error paths in the magic+version preamble, and\nthe bounds checks introduced by the d6b96f7 (frankentorch-sre)\nhalf-dtype work.\n\nNew SafeTensors fuzz target: `fuzz_targets/ft_serialize_safetensors.rs`\nexercises `load_safetensors_from_bytes` \u2014 the second exposed parser in\nft-serialize, with zero prior fuzz coverage. Seeded with 15 inputs:\n\n  empty file (no tensors)\n  empty file with __metadata__\n  scalar F64 [1] / F32 [3] / F16 [2,2] / BF16 [4]\n  multiple tensors with mixed dtypes (offset-map exercise)\n  zero-numel tensor [3,0,5]\n  large 1D F32 [1024]\n  unsupported dtype (I64) \u2014 exercises ft-serialize's reject path\n  unicode tensor name (\"\u03b1\")\n  corrupted: header_size larger than file\n  corrupted: header is invalid JSON\n  corrupted: data_offsets exceed binary length\n  composite F16 + BF16 + F32 with metadata\n\nTwo new ft-serialize unit tests guard the corpora against future\npanic-on-input regressions:\n\n  fuzz_corpus_safetensors_does_not_panic\n  fuzz_corpus_state_dict_does_not_panic\n\nEach test walks the on-disk corpus directory, loads every seed, and\nasserts the loader either returns Ok or a graceful Err \u2014 never\nunwinds. This catches a corpus<->loader skew at `cargo test` time\nlong before the fuzzer is invoked.\n\nft-serialize: 68 tests pass (66 prior + 2 new). Clippy + ubs clean.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
  "files": [
